**Title:** COM - Hardware Community

**Description:**
The Hardware Hacking Community (HHC) is a place for hardware enthusiasts to learn, solder, and create electronic projects. 

**Main Activities:**
- Participants can solder mini badges and other projects during the conference.
- Tables, chairs, soldering tools (irons, solder, wick, vacuum pump), and other supplies will be provided.
- A "How to solder" class will be held.

**What to Bring:**
- Attendees are encouraged to bring their own electronic components or projects to work on.

**Hours of Operation:**
- Monday: Closed
- Tuesday: 10:30 AM - 5:00 PM
- Wednesday: 10:30 AM - 5:00 PM
- Thursday: 9:00 AM - 5:00 PM
- Friday: 9:00 AM - 11:00 AM

**Skills Learned:**
- Basic Hardware Structure
- Soldering Skills
- PCB Assembly Skills
- Electronic Components Identification

**Tools Available:**
- Oscilloscopes
- Multi-Meters
- Bus Pirates

**MiniBadge Details:**
- A MiniBadge will be available for attendees, with details to be announced at the booth.

